      <section eId="sec_CHC-705">
        <num>CHC 705</num>
        <heading>705. Â Notice; right to be heard</heading>
        <subsection eId="CHC-705__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The department shall give notice of the right to appear at each permanency hearing to any foster parent, pre-adoptive parent, or relative providing care for the child.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-705__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The notice shall state the date, time, and place of the permanency hearing and the recipient's right to attend and be heard.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-705__subsec_C">
          <num>C.</num>
          <content>
            <p>If a foster parent, pre-adoptive parent, or relative providing care for the child fails to appear at a permanency hearing, the department shall report to the court whether notice was given or, if not, what diligent efforts were made to locate and notify the absent person. The court may permit the hearing to be held in the person's absence.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CHC-705__subsec_D">
          <num>D.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The court shall solicit and consider information regarding the care and treatment of the child from any foster parent, pre-adoptive parent, or relative providing care for the child who appears for the hearing.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=73301</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
